  ultimately bear on the nature of degrees. In this talk I’ll consider how
  this problem might be approached if degrees are understood in terms of
  kinds, and what that might predict about anaphora to conjoined adjectives
  (e.g. _Donald is ignorant and unpleasant, and his son even more so_).
  
