  (abs): Degree readings of size adjectives, as in _big idiot_,
  cannot be explained as merely a consequence of vagueness or as an
  extra-grammatical phenomenon. Rather, they reflect the grammatical
  architecture of nominal gradability. Such readings are available only for
  size adjectives in attributive positions, and systematically only for
  adjectives that predicate bigness. These restrictions can be understood
